===Console Commands===
Those commands available to use on console.
{| class="wikitable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed"
|+
! Command !! Description
|-
| /time set <H> <M> <S> || Time setting, minutes/seconds can be skipped. 
Command forces manual time setting mode.
|-
| /time mul <Multiplier> || Time multiplier designation (Based on 24 hours)  0~9999,
Command forces manual time setting mode.

(For a 30 minute cycle, this is 48 times the real time, so: /time mul 48)
|-
| /ssw || Toggle SSW Mode
Graphics Preset Auto Specify function for Virtual Desktop SSW function. 

Half of the standard FPS is set for estimation.
|-
| /walk || Slow Walk Mode
Walking Speed get reduced to half than default.
|-
| /qe || Toggle Keyboard Swivel Mode
Option to swivel keyboard with the “Q” and “E” keys on the keyboard.
|-
| /darknight || Toggle Night Ambient Light Intensity Suppression Mode
Dims ambient light at night (Especially in areas away from the center of city)
|-
| /ao || Toggle Screen Space Ambient Occlusion (Multi Scale Volumetric Obscurance)
Visually better, but AO is misaligned when using VR mode. 

Automatically disabled /sao or /pao if enabled
|-
| /pao || Toggle Projector-based Ambient Occlusion
MSVO get performed on the building only, result get projected by a projector.

Does not affect the avatar and does not shift like when /ao in used with a VR Camera.

Workload is high due to projection. 

Automatically disabled /ao or /sao if enabled.
|-
| /sao || Toggle Screen Space Ambient Occlusion (Scalable Ambient Obscurance)
May flicker, but AO will not shift when taking pictures in VR mode. 

Automatically disabled /ao or /pao if enabled.
|-
| /fps || Toggle Frame Rate Graph
Toggle frame rate graph on Mini Map.
|-
| /dev || Toggle Developer Mode
All player coordinate periodic log output and more...
|-
| /kick <ID> || For Admin, Kick Specified Player. (Not in Use)
|-
| /rstcar || For Admin, Reset Car Position.
|-
| /rstcam || For Admin, Reset Synced Camera Position.
|}
