==Time==

There are three modes of time provided in this world.

* '''30 Minutes Cycle''': One day passes in 30 minutes, which is the default setting of this world. The world time will be the same regardless of time zone.
* '''Real-Time''': Time will follow your PC clock.
* '''Manual''': Manually set time by hand. You can set time by slider or command.

==Teleportation==

Several teleportation methods are offered in the world. 

Some exist for warping to rooftops or special warp functions, but here we mention those for shortcuts in movement.

* '''Public Telephones''': By interacting with a public telephone in the world, you can warp to a telephone tower at a telephone station. And vice versa.
* '''Public Restrooms''': Entering and exiting the back room of a public restroom in the world will warp you to a different public restroom.
* '''Teleport to User''': Teleportation for any user is implemented (opt-out).

